<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="613" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d613">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 441.11B74/20</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-29">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 29, 1915</hi>.</date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 12.30 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2189. Your 1512, 6th.<note n="1" xml:id="d613fn1">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_381">p.
                                    381</ref>.</note> In reply to my representations regarding <hi rend="italic">Segurança</hi> Foreign Office advises me that
                                instructions have been sent to British Ambassador at Washington to
                                inform British consuls that, to minimize the risks of delay and
                                detention, it would be advisable that shippers should arrange to
                                have their cargoes for Holland consigned to the Netherlands Oversea
                                Trust.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>